
## ü§ù Contributing

We welcome contributions from anyone who wants to help improve this project!  

Before submitting a contribution, please follow these guidelines:

1. **Fork the repository** and create your branch:
   ```bash
   git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
   ```
2. Make your changes and ensure the code is clean and well-commented.

3. Test your changes locally to make sure nothing breaks.

4. Commit your changes with a clear message:
    ```bash
    git commit -m "Add a meaningful commit message"
    ```
5. Push your branch to your forked repository:
    ```bash
    git push origin feature/your-feature-name
    ```
6. Open a Pull Request (PR) in the main repository. Describe your changes clearly and provide any necessary context.


